    "body": "This happens occasionally with the Quicknode infrastructure for various reasons.\r\n\r\nOnce we have https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/pull/1638 merged, we can take back our DNS, it is currently a `CNAME` to Quicknode\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n$ dig mainnet.optimism.io\r\n...\r\n;; QUESTION SECTION:\r\n;mainnet.optimism.io.\t\tIN\tA\r\n\r\n;; ANSWER SECTION:\r\nmainnet.optimism.io.\t300\tIN\tCNAME\tdawn-bold-frog.optimism.quiknode.pro.\r\ndawn-bold-frog.optimism.quiknode.pro. 60 IN A\t143.244.182.79\r\n...\r\n```\r\n\r\nWe will be able to set a `mainnet.optimism.io` `A` record to a load balanced rpcproxyd where it is configured to send read requests to quicknode and write requests to the sequencer. Currently, quicknode receives all traffic via `mainnet.optimism.io` and then forwards write requests back to the sequencer.\r\n\r\nThis should fix the intermittent problems with `mainnet.optimism.io` and we will be able to very easily introspect errors since all traffic is coming through Optimism infra.\r\n\r\ncc @optimisticben @mslipper ",
